  "prompt": "Can allergies cause dizziness and head pressure?",
  "response": "Yes, allergies can cause symptoms such as dizziness and head pressure. Allergic reactions can lead to nasal congestion and sinus inflammation, which can impact the inner ear and contribute to these sensations. When the sinuses are congested, the pressure can cause discomfort in the head and lead to feelings of dizziness. Additionally, allergies can trigger histamine release, which might affect blood flow and contribute to dizziness.\n\nIf you are experiencing these symptoms, it is important to consult with a healthcare professional to determine the cause and appropriate treatment. They can help identify if allergies are indeed the cause or if there are other underlying conditions that need to be addressed.",
